/*!
    \page bobuiconcurrent-index.html
    \title BobUI Concurrent

    \brief The BobUI Concurrent module contains functionality to support concurrent execution of program code.


    The BobUI Concurrent module provides high-level APIs that make it
    possible to write multi-threaded programs without using low-level
    threading primitives such as mutexes, read-write locks, wait
    conditions, or semaphores. Programs written with BobUI Concurrent
    automatically adjust the number of threads used according to the
    number of processor cores available. This means that applications
    written today will continue to scale when deployed on multi-core
    systems in the future.

    BobUI Concurrent includes functional programming style APIs for
    parallel list processing, including a MapReduce and FilterReduce
    implementation for shared-memory (non-distributed) systems, and
    classes for managing asynchronous computations in GUI
    applications:

    \list
    \li \l {Concurrent Map and Map-Reduce}
        \list
            \li \l {BobUIConcurrent::map}{BobUIConcurrent::map()} applies a function
                to every item in a container, modifying the items in-place.
            \li \l {BobUIConcurrent::mapped}{BobUIConcurrent::mapped()} is like
                map(), except that it returns a new container with the
                modifications.
            \li \l {BobUIConcurrent::mappedReduced}{BobUIConcurrent::mappedReduced()}
                is like mapped(), except that the modified results are reduced
                or folded into a single result.
        \endlist

    \li \l {Concurrent Filter and Filter-Reduce}
    \list
        \li \l {BobUIConcurrent::filter}{BobUIConcurrent::filter()} removes all items
            from a container based on the result of a filter function.
        \li \l {BobUIConcurrent::filtered}{BobUIConcurrent::filtered()} is like
            filter(), except that it returns a new container with the filtered
            results.
        \li \l {BobUIConcurrent::filteredReduced}{BobUIConcurrent::filteredReduced()}
            is like filtered(), except that the filtered results are reduced or
            folded into a single result.
    \endlist

    \li \l {Concurrent Run}
    \list
        \li \l {BobUIConcurrent::run}{BobUIConcurrent::run()} runs a function in
            another thread.
    \endlist

    \li \l {Concurrent Task}
    \list
        \li \l {BobUIConcurrent::task}{BobUIConcurrent::task()} creates an instance
